article.description: Curtis Phillips scored 15 of his 20 points in the second half and Tennessee Tech scored 11 of their final 15 points in the last two minutes from the foul line to defeat Lipscomb 86-80 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Phillips, free throws lift Tennessee Tech by Lipscomb 86-80
article.linkText: Phillips, free throws lift Tennessee Tech by Lipscomb 86-80
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- Curtis Phillips scored 15 of his 20 points in the second half and Tennessee Tech scored 11 of their final 15 points in the last two minutes from the foul line to defeat Lipscomb 86-80 on Wednesday night. Mason Ramsey and Stephaun Adams added 15 points apiece for the Eagles (7-1), who went 23 of 30 from the line after intermission and 37 of 49 for the game for their best start in 12 years. Garrison Mathews had 18 points, Kenny Cooper 16 and Rob Marberry 15 for the Bison (4-3), who were 13 of 24 from the line. The teams combined for 56 fouls, 73 free throws and 37 turnovers while going a combined 8 of 40 from 3-point range. However, Lipscomb shot 59 percent and Tennessee Tech 56 percent from the field in the second half despite a combined 2 of 15 behind the arc. Lipscomb was within four on Aaron Korn's layup with 1:03 to go but after Adams made two free throws the Bison missed a 3. Phillips converted with a layup and then the Bison missed two more from distance before Adams made a pair of free throws with 27 seconds left to seal it.
